<dl id="n53122h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53122h">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53122h"> 122(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> fruits ripen at birth, <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n53122h"><li>FW 59.11 </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/lexc.htm#n53122h">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/l39c.htm#n53122h">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n53122h">MS BL 47476b-177</ms> </li><li>JJA 49:375 <a name="cd10" href="../../ff/fdra/cda.htm#cd10">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/c/cd10.htm#n53122h">Draft: I.3&sect;1.10</a>/2.10/3.10</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"><mark>En ce moment m&ecirc;me</mark>, tous les vivants fr&eacute;mirent de joie. La terre trembla. Dans le ciel, on entendit des chants et des danses. Les arbres de toutes les saisons se couvrirent de fleurs &eacute;panouies et <mark>de fruits m&ucirc;rs</mark>. Des rayons d&apos;une puret&eacute; sereine illumin&egrave;rent le ciel. Les malades n&apos;&eacute;pro&uuml;v&egrave;rent plus de souffrances. Les affam&eacute;s se sentirent rassasi&eacute;s. Ceux qu&apos;avaient &eacute;gar&eacute;s les liqueurs virent tomber leur ivresse. Les fous recouvr&egrave;rent la raison. Les infirmes furent sains de corps. Les pauvres trouv&egrave;rent de l&apos;or. Les portes des prisons s&apos;ouvrirent. Les m&eacute;chants ne connurent plus le mal. <small> A. Ferdinand Herold, <a name="AFHB" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#AFHB"><cite title="source">La Vie Du Bouddha</cite></a> (1922) 16</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: At the birth, trees of all seasons bore flowers and their fruits ripened. The child was named Siddharta and this was his royal name and his family name was Gautama. </mm> </dd></dl>
